            <bioghist>
                <p>Aaron Tilton was the proprietor of a general goods store in West Boylston,
                    Massachusetts. </p>
            </bioghist>

            <scopecontent>
                <p>This account book records sales of sundry commodities including: rum, calico,
                    sugar, pine boards, tobacco, salt, shoes, gloves, and brandy from 1824 to
                    1828.</p>
            </scopecontent>


